OL,7,FHe argued the company is meeting that
OL,8,Fhourly rate when factoring in holiday
OL,9,Fpay, guaranteed overtime and bonuses
OL,10,Fbut admitted he could not live on the
OL,11,Fwage himself.
OL,13,FHebblethwaite said: "It's important we
OL,14,Fcompare apples with apples. Exchange
OL,15,Frates move about.
OL,17,F"We pay in excess of those standards
OL,18,Fwhere we are governed by international
OL,19,Flaws. There is a minimum basic wage,
OL,20,Fdependent of exchange rate, which is
OL,21,Fabout #2.18.
